 corresponding to the strange quark mass.\nHence, a more precise determination of the strange quark mass can test this\nmodel. For the best fit point, we find the effective Majorana neutrino mass of\n$m_{\\beta\\beta} = 0.22$ meV and the sum of light neutrino masses as $\\Sigma =\n0.078$ eV, which are consistent with the current constraints from the search\nfor the neutrinoless double beta decay and the CMB anisotropy measurement.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 5 Jul 2019 17:32:10 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 11 Jul 2019 02:32:29 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 4 Oct 2019 05:12:10 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Tue, 10 Mar 2020 10:42:12 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-03-17"}
