 with those of previous works, although we reach deeper surface\nbrightness levels, so that the PSF effects are stronger. We obtain scale\nheights and mass ratios of thin and thick discs ($z_{{\\rm t}}$, $z_{{\\rm T}}$,\nand $M_{{\\rm T}}/M_{{\\rm t}}$), which provide excellent agreement with previous\nstudies. Our small initial sample provides evidence for aspects of a wide\nvariety of formation theories for the thick discs in disc galaxies.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 5 Jul 2019 18:46:14 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 29 Jul 2019 12:57:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-08-28"}
