 Er$^{3+}$ takes on a strong XY single-ion anisotropy in\nK$_3$Er(VO$_4$)$_2$, leading to vanishing moments when pseudo-spins are\noriented along c. Thus, the magnetic structure, when considered from the\npseudo-spin point of view comprises alternating layers of b-axis and c-axis\naligned antiferromagnetism.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 5 Jul 2019 20:32:23 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 23 Jul 2020 17:57:09 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-09-23"}
